fields.name: Midterm comments
fields.description_text: Comment the midterm scores divided by topic
fields.text_content:
Dear {{ GivenName }}

Here are the comments about your answers to the midterm exam (ordered by topic).

Chemistry and Molecules of Life

{% if T1_LOW %}You need to review the concepts in this topic. It is important that you identify those molecules that are important in a living organism, and differentiate them from other molecules. Also, make sure you review the basic steps of the chemical reactions we discussed in class.{% endif %}

{% if T1_MID %}You need to review this topic again. Make sure you easily identify which molecules are present, for example, inside a cell and differentiate them from other.{% endif %}

{% if T1_HIGH %}Good work with this topic!{% endif %}

Cell function and structure

{% if T2_LOW %}Go back and review in depth this chapter. You need to be able to identify the parts of the cell, and more importantly, the role they play in the various functions. It may help to build first a table of these functions, then a table of the parts of the cell, and then a paragraph in each category connecting one element from each table.{% endif %}

{% if T2_MID %}You need to review the cell function and structure. You confused some of the parts and you need to make sure you are sure about all the functions and the parts that participate in each of them.{% endif %}

{% if T2_HIGH %}Good work with this material! Can you envision how the cell gets the basic blocks for some of the functions such as DNA duplication?{% endif %}

Nutrition, Metabolism & Enzymes

{% if T3_LOW %}Take another thorough review of this block. You need to connect the elements required in the cell to perform nutrition processes with the components required, and more importantly, with the enzymes that regulate these processes.{% endif %}

{% if T3_MID %}You need to go back and review a bit more this part. Look again at the various processes that comprise what we call the metabolism of the cell, and the role of each enzyme in these processes.{% endif %}

{% if T3_HIGH %}Good work with this block. Can you envision which metabolic processes will be affected if there are not enough nutrients reaching the cell? Can you think of any disease that is connected to these elements?{% endif %}

Cell Division

{% if T4_LOW %}You need to review the material about mitosis and meiosis. The two processes have analogies and differences, you have to be able to analyse the steps and connect them with the other elements in the cell that participate.{% endif %}

{% if T4_MID %}Good work with this topic, but you still need to review the material because some of the questions were not correctly answered. See if you can draw a diagram of the ttwo processes (mitosis and meiosis) without looking at the notes.{% endif %}

{% if T4_HIGH %}Good work with this block!{% endif %}

DNA Structure and Replication

{% if T5_LOW %}Go back and review the structure of the DNA and its replication process. You need to be able to identify the different parts of the molecule, the basic elements, and how are they connected. Additionally, you need to be able to explain in detail the replication process.{% endif %}

{% if T5_MID %}You need to review a bit more this block. Make sure you understand the role of each of the parts of the molecule with the replication process.{% endif %}

{% if T5_HIGH %}Good work with this topic. Can you identify anomalies that may appear during the replication process?{% endif %}

Your total score for the midterm is {{ Total }}.

Kind regards

{{ Coordinator name }}

{{ Course name }}

The presentation had a clearly defined structure: setting the problem, describing the methodology, results and conclusion. It was delivered clearly and in the allotted time.
fields.feedback_text: Good job with the presentation. You included the expected blocks (problem description, methodology, results and conclusions) and it was delivered clearly and in the allotted time.

fields.description_text: The presentation either had an incomplete structure, was not clearly delivered, or it was not finished in the allotted time.
fields.feedback_text: Think about the three requirements for this presentation: structure (introduce the problem, present the methodology, results, and conclusions), deliver it clearly, and in the allotted time. There were some aspects of it that needed improvement. For future presentations, review your material to make sure you cover all the required blocks and practice to make sure it is clearly delivered and within the allotted time.

fields.description_text: The presentation has some substantial room or improvement. The structure is far from complete, it was not delivered clearly, or the time allotted was not respected.
fields.feedback_text: The presentation could be significantly improved. Make sure you review the structure again and verify that the problem is clearly stated, then the method, followed by the results and then the conclusions. The presentation needs to be clear and understandable, and it must fit in the allotted time. For future presentations, make sure you rehearse it paying attention to these requirements.

fields.description_text: The project is well written with the expected sections and the right content. An introduction with the description of the problem, a methodology describing the steps to obtain the results, a result section, and a conclusion section connecting the results with the problem.
fields.feedback_text: Good work with the document. The sections have the right content and are coherently written.

fields.description_text: The structure of the document needs some improvement. Some of the sections do not contain the right information or not in the right format.
fields.feedback_text: Review the document again and make sure that the introduction describes the problem, then the methodology section describes the steps to get the results, the result section just describes the information collected, and the conclusions connect the results with the problem.

fields.description_text: The structure of the document has several deficiencies. Either the introduction fails to situate the problem, or the methodology does not include a clear description of the steps to obtain the results, or the results are not clearly expected, or the conclusions are not properly written.
fields.feedback_text: The document needs a significant revision. Remember that the introduction section needs to presents the problem and its context, the methodology focuses on the steps you have taken to collect the results, the result section presents the data you obtained, and the conclusions connect the data with the problem. Give the document another review to make sure its structure follows these guidelines.
